observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Management:
Create an Inventory Committee who shall be responsible for the actual count to ascertain the existence, completeness and condition of all PPEs owned by the Municipality, and for the preparation of the RPCPPE;
Instruct the Inventory Committee to follow the prescribed format for the preparation of RPCPPE to ensure inclusion of all necessary and relevant information therein, and submit the same to the Accounting Office for reconciliation;
Require the Property/Supply Unit to render a report of all defective or non-functional PPE items for proper recording and disposal using the Inventory and Inspection Report of Unserviceable Property (IIRUP); and
Refer to COA Circular No. 2020-006 dated January 31, 2020 on the specific guidelines and procedures to assist the LGU in coming up with reliable PPE balances that are verifiable as to existence, condition and accountability.

We recommended that Management:

Submit the said lacking documentary requirements as shown in the attached schedule;

Comply with the posting requirements provided under GPPB-TSO Advisory No. 05-2020 on the procurement projects undertaken through Emergency Procurement under the Bayanihan Act;

Require the Municipal Accountant to meticulously review and ensure completeness and propriety of the required supporting documents for all related disbursements in accordance with the applicable laws, rules and regulations.

We recommended that Management:

Observe the perpetual inventory method in accounting of inventories;

Prepare and maintain the required forms, subsidiary records and periodic reports, such as SLC, SC, RIS and RSMI, as prescribed in the Government Accounting Manual for LGUs;

Conduct periodic physical count of inventories to determine any necessary adjustments in the books and inventory records.

We recommended that Management:

Require all transfer of funds to Barangays be covered by a Memorandum of Agreement and other documentary requirements as enumerated in Section 3.1.1 of COA Circular No. 2012-001 to establish accountability and monitor the utilization of the funds;

Direct the Municipal Accountant to prepare adjusting entries of the affected accounts to recognize receivables from the barangays;

Require the recipient barangays for the liquidation of the fund transferred;

Submit justification / explanation why the reprogramming of appropriations was not covered by an approved ordinance by way of a supplemental budget; and

Ensure strict compliance with the applicable laws, rules and regulations on fund transfers and budgetary realignments.

Establish a clear-cut policy on the grant of AICS setting forth specific guidelines on the use of funds and standard procedures to properly implement the provision of AICS of the Municipality to its constituents;

Ensure that the assessment should be centralized and made by qualified personnel under the office of MSWD after checking and reproduction of all supporting documents to the claim; and

Create a mechanism to monitor and control the grant of financial assistance.

Require the concerned official and employee to refund the financial assistance/honorarium irregularly paid in the total amount of ₱48,000.00;

Likewise, stop the practice of granting financial assistance/honorarium which are not in accord to guidelines, rules and regulations; and

Ensure completeness of the supporting documents for claims and ascertain the validity, propriety and legality of the transactions.

